    	<h2><a name="2003-03-10" href="#2003-03-10"><font color="#660000">2003-03-10</font></a></h2>
   	

	<div class="posts">
	<a name="90487910">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://www.west-wind.com/">West Wind Technologies - Making waves on the Web</a>.&nbsp; A web site I found as the result of an outstanding article on DevX showing how to do dynamic execution using .NET and even run the equivalent of ASP.NET as part of a standalong .NET application.  This looks like just what I am looking for in making CD-ROMs of web sites that work just like mirrors of the site.&nbsp; Something I am anxious to explore further in the next few weeks.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#90487910">Monday, March 10, 2003</a></span></div>
<br>
  <!-- 2002-11-08 Change date format to yyyy-mm-dd and bookmark it 
                2002-11-09 Tune the color and make a purplized link out of it -->
	
